---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="About — astro-build-demo">
  <article class="prose max-w-none py-8">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>
      This repo holds an Astro project. The source lives in <code>/src</code>,
      the compiled site lives in <code>/docs</code>, and both are committed so
      the pre-build and post-build content live side by side.
    </p>
    <p>
      To change something, edit any file under <code>/src</code> via the GitHub
      web UI, then ask Claude Code to pull the repo and rebuild. It runs
      <code>npm run build</code> in its sandbox and commits the updated
      <code>/docs</code>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Never edit <code>/docs</code> by hand. It is generated output, and the
      next build will quietly overwrite your changes.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
